com.google.code.gwt.database.client
Class SQLResultSetRowList<T extends JavaScriptObject>

java.lang.Object
  com.google.code.gwt.database.client.SQLResultSetRowList<T>
Type Parameters:
T - specified the type to represent a row in the ResultSet. It must be a subclass of JavaScriptObject. You could use GenericRow as a sensible default.
All Implemented Interfaces:
Iterable<T>
public final class SQLResultSetRowList<T extends JavaScriptObject>
extends Object
implements Iterable<T>

Represents a tabular resultset much like JDBC's ResultSet.

The object type of the row returned by getItem(int) is specified as the generic type accompanying this class, which is eventually specified at the StatementCallback interface. You can use GenericRow as a dynamic object type.

See Also:
GenericRow, StatementCallback, W3C Web Database - SQLResultSetRowList
